            <p><span style="font-family: 'Glass Antiqua', cursive; font-size: 48px;">O</span>n the 22nd of Obsidian, darkness descends over the fortress. The words are bleak, so this historian will quote them directly: "oh shit a forgotten beast was in the cave and is fucking Gylis up. Mighty stone door is locked behind him." While this historian commends Overload for protecting his people, she shudders at the thought of sacrificing a man to a beast without even attempting a rescue, particularly since there is a standing army that is clearly capable of killing beasts.</p>
			<p><div class="thumb-right"><a href="images/suc_img/year2_6.png"><img src="images/suc_img/year2_6.png" /></a>Goblins!!</div><span style="font-family: 'Glass Antiqua', cursive; font-size: 48px;">G</span>ylis is killed by the forgotten beast on the 23rd of Obsidian. Overload does not pause in his entry for this man whatsoever, but his reason may be valid. On the same day, goblins ambush the fortress. There may be no time for mourning.</p>
